The Human Realms and the Demon Marches
Today, the former Vel’thorne territories are divided among fifteen human kingdoms. Three of them border the demonic lands directly, while twelve others lie farther north and inland. Internal rivalries and shifting alliances among all fifteen are constant, and many fear that a new continental war between humans could erupt at any moment.
Each kingdom follows a classical feudal structure:

Duchy (Ruler: Duke) — The largest and most powerful feudal territories. Often nearly autonomous, containing multiple subordinate regions. Dukes are usually blood relatives of the monarch.
County (Ruler: Count) — The standard administrative division. Counts maintain order, collect taxes, and raise troops. They may answer to a duke or directly to the king.
Viscounty (Ruler: Viscount) — Often a deputy territory assisting a count, though some exist as independent holdings.
Barony (Ruler: Baron) — The basic land unit, ranging from single villages to clusters of manors.
Baronet — A hereditary honor title above knights but below barons. May or may not include land.
Landed Knights — Granted estates in exchange for military service.
Household Knights — Landless knights serving directly in a lord’s retinue.
Hedge Knights / Sworn Swords — Landless wanderers who sell their blades or seek fortune in tournaments.

On every contested border — especially those between human kingdoms — lie Marches ruled by Margraves. These frontier lords command larger garrisons and enjoy greater autonomy due to the constant threat of invasion. The most powerful and prestigious Marches guard the demonic border.
Between the stable human kingdoms and demonic territories lies a dangerous Buffer Zone of ungoverned lands, ruined free cities with broken gates, and wild marches. This region is infested with bandits, monsters, rogue mages, and occasional demonic warbands. It serves as both a shield and a lawless frontier where fortune-seekers and exiles thrive — or die.
The border itself has been relatively calm for the past decade — one of many such “lows” that have occurred hundreds of times since the first invasions. These periods of uneasy peace are always explained by fresh infighting among the Demon Lords and Hell Princes. When one emerges dominant or a temporary truce forms in the infernal realms, raids and incursions inevitably resume.
